   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>As All the Divine Attributes and</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>All the Human Virtues</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Christ is all the divine attributes and all the human virtues.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Whatever God is in His being is an attribute.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>God is holy and God is righteous; therefore, holiness and righteousness are two of His divine attributes.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>He is love, light, life, redemption, salvation, power, and strength.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>All of these items are divine attributes.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Attributes are different from virtues.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Attributes are the things which belong to us as our possession; virtues are the things we possess that are expressed for others' appreciation.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>God is love.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>When love is expressed for others' appreciation, it becomes a virtue.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>According to 1 Peter 2:9, we are a royal priesthood to tell out the virtues of Him who has called us out of darkness into His marvelous light.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Christ is all of the divine attributes and the human virtues.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>As the One Who Is Unsearchable and</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Untraceable in His Riches</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Christ is rich and His riches are unsearchable and untraceable Eph 3:8 , indicating that He Himself is unsearchable and untraceable.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>As the One Who Is Sufficient in His Grace</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>He is also sufficient in His grace 2 Cor 12:9 .</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The grace of Christ is sufficient.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>This grace is the processed Triune God given to us for our enjoyment and supply.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>In such a grace Christ is sufficient to meet our various kinds of need.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>As the One Who Gives the Spirit Not by Measure</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Because Christ is unsearchable, He gives the Spirit not by measure John 3:34 .</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>This means that the Spirit given by Him is also unsearchable as He is.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>As the Life-Giving Spirit the Spirit</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Christ is the life-giving Spirit the Spirit 1 Cor 15:45b; 2 Cor 3:17 .</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Christ is not only the Son embodied to be a man, but has also become the Spirit in His resurrection; hence, He is the Spirit, the pneumatic Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>As Our Life</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Christ is our life Col 3:4a .</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>He is the divine life John 11:25; 14:6 coming into us to be our life; hence, we live by Him John 14:19 .</S>
   </TEXT>
